Title: Twisted Lies (Twisted, #4)
Author: Ana Huang
My Review: The problem I have with the male protagonists in this series is that they are all supposed to be this like brooding dark magnetic men that scream "I can't be fixed but you can try".... but they are all actually the most insufferable, unlikeable characters I've seen.. ESPECIALLY this one! There's something diabolical about a man who doesn't believe in love seeing a women who wants to fall in love and then deciding "I want her and no one else can have her" WHILE knowing he can't offer her what she wants,,, like you fool???

Title: Local Woman Missing
Author: Mary Kubica
My Review: Ok so I LOVED this book!! It wasn't too dark (Pretty Girls by Karin Slaughter was very good but it nearly turned me away from this genre because it was so graphic) and there was just enough suggestion to let the reader assume what happened. This book was perfectly paced until the end :(( I felt the ending was a bit rushed especially with the reveal of what happened to Delilah. I think some of it was a bit far fetched like the cop lying about the dna test like that was terrible and Bea managing to keep a child in her garage for 11 years without anyone noticing.

My Review:
1. Fake dating tropes are fun but the miscommunication has to be just done right or else it becomes insufferable. I understand her reasoning not telling Adam about T*m but it shouldn't have been her main one.
2. She's bold, kisses random man, but also like ,,,, can't tell Adam that she has a crush on him. Like idk girlie why can't you just tell him!!!
3. But it's such a cute book and as a former wanna be immunology girl who did an immunology internship at one of the schools mentioned, I absolutely loved loved loved the setting and loved that I knew all the methods and understood what certain test were like Omg!!
